==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Theorist
<hw>The"o*rist</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>th⟦eacute⟧oriste</ets>.]</ety> <def>One who forms theories; one
given to theory and speculation; a speculatist.</def>
<rj><au>Cowper.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The greatest <qex>theoretists</qex> have given the preference to
such a government as that which obtains in this kingdom.</q>
<rj><qau>Addison.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><-- 2. A scientist who forms theories about natural phenomena, based
on the data gathered by others, rather than himself performing
experiments to test the theories. Contrasted with experimentalist.
-->⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Theorization</ent>⟦br⟧
